The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, March 25: The Authority of Advance Rulings (Income Tax) has ruled that Mauritius-based firms will not have to pay capital gains tax in the country. The decision will encourage global business entities to route investment from Mauritius. We uphold the contention of the applicant that by virtue of the India-Mauritius double tax avoidance agreement, capital gains tax is not liable to be charged in India, it said.                             
	 New Delhi, March 25: The Supreme Court has said an insurance firm cannot deny claim to a vehicle owner just because the insured car met with an accident when it was given on hire to some other person.                             
	 Mumbai, March 25: The RBI has asked all its regional offices and banks conducting government business to extend their working hours on March 30 and 31 to meet the rush of tax payers in view of the closing of this fiscal year.                            
	 New Delhi, March 25: India has announced duty concessions on import of toothpaste, footwear, imitation jewellery and water heaters from Bhutan, Bangladesh, the Maldives and Nepal.                            
	 Mumbai, March 25: The State Bank of India has hinted that it may retain its home loan scheme offering 8 per cent interest rate with slight modifications.                                                                                                                          
